6. Sides of pronotum in female and often in male centrally with transverse striae that extend backwards to upper part (
Fig. 5G
); white stripe on pronotum in male and female wider, about as wide as the width of fore femur (
Fig. 5G
); mid coxae in female with extensive yellow or whitish marks on outer side (absent in small females); pale marks along inner orbits above antennal scrobes in female usually stouter, about 2.0 times as long as wide, slightly widened in upper part, rounded (
